Why do we adding `new Throwable()` to the log? I guess, it isn't useful because it doesn't have any information. Instead, I would log `toString()` of the transaction, which may have more useful information. I.e. something like:
```
if (log.isDebugEnabled()) {
    log.debug("Transaction is still open. Rolling back the transaction: "+tx.toString());
}
```

