timeline.body:
We have multiple same `finally` blocks. I propose to move the same code into a separate method. I.e.:
```
private void rollbackIfNotNull(BaseTransaction tx){
    if (tx != null) {
        try {
            if (log.isDebugEnabled()) {
                log.debug("Transaction is still open. Rolling back the transaction: "+tx.toString());
            }
            tx.rollback();
        } catch (Throwable e) {
            //TODO: We need to handle the transaction newTx which potentially may leak into memory
            log.error("Failed to rollback the transaction "+tx.toString()+". The transaction now may be leaked into memory.", e);
        }
    }
}
```

After that we can change all places where you added `finally` like the next:
```
finally {
  rollbackIfNotNull(newTx);
}
```

